{"author":{"id":"bf52274e4b8baa03d436abcc532c02b6a719b9a772a7e952e18fcc8627570e5f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770387526,"nonce":"Tn04TPDuMV3t1g6VijjgE77ja1s=","title":"Allow literal numbers in command #:run field","message":"Literal numbers in the `#:run` field of commands should be accepted and automagically converted to strings. At the moment, they error out. Example below:\n```\n;; foo.scm\n(command #:inputs (message #:type string)\n         #:run \"echo\" message 1)\n```\n```\n$ ccwl compile foo.scm\nfoo.scm:2:30: error: Invalid command element 1. Command elements must either be input identifiers or literal strings.\n    1 | (command #:inputs (message #:type string)\n    2 |          #:run \"echo\" message 1)\n```","files":null}]}